text: 🌿PLANTII SPRING CLEANING🌿 This used to be one of my favorite rooms in the house.  Just by walking by and seeing how pretty all the plants were, it would put me in a better mood. I don’t know what it is lately… if it’s the weather, seasonal depression, or something else but my plants were starting to look like howI felt: sad and droopy.  Although I had no motivation to do so, I knew I had to get up and make a change. I started by taking everything out of the room and disassembling the plant shelf. I then went in and cleaned all of the walls and baseboards, and then swept the floors and swiffered. I grabbed my favorite wood spray From @methodproducts and wiped down all of the shelves and wood crates. I love this spray, because it not only makes the wood shine, but it also makes the whole house smell so good. I then reassembled the shelf in a different formation. I grabbed all the plants and pruned watered and fertilized them and then put them back on the shelf in new places. I added the rest of the furniture back into the room and voilà!  The room looks better, smells great and makes me smile when I walk by again. If the sun could just come back now it would be perfect!  Also, if you have kids or pets I highly recommend the broom I used in this video. It has a rubber brush that catches all of the hair, crumbs, dirt, etc. It makes sweeping so much cleaner and faster.  #diy #plants #plantcare #springcleaning
